{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Specifically protect people's political views under discrimination law",
        "additional_details": "As it stands the Equality Act 2010 only protects people for the following; age, disability, gender reassignment, marriage and civil partnership, pregnancy and maternity, race, religion or belief, sex & sexual orientation.\r\n\r\nThis leaves a hole for people to potentially be unfairly dismissed from the jobs or be unable to secure employment because they have a different political view.\r\n\r\nHow can people be free to choose the political preference when there is a risk of losing their livelihoods.",
        "background": "The government should amend the Equality Act 2010 to specifically include Political Views to prevent people from losing their jobs because of which side of politics they align with.",
